text:
Good neighbourhood mall, will living essentials shops, as and when kiosk available.
Mi xue, lihor,koi is around the area.
Our PM area.

The place has been constantly renovated to the point that you can find almost anything here. There are plenty of options for dining. The Fairprice and Fairprice Finest make shopping for urgent groceries extremely easy.

The food here is fabulous. Love the mee hun kueh and big pai at Nam kee. The toast box and Ya Kun for the coffee, half boil egg and toast bread. The Yu Kee duck rice is delicious, too. There are too many to choice.

Typical HDB heartland shopping mall. Probably the only place in the whole of Singapore where you have an wet market just next to the MRT station. It means it is super convenient to buy your groceries, hop into the train and home you go. Coming back to the mall called Yew Tee Point, which is also next to the MRT station, this makes super convenient for the residents staying around here to get whatever they needed back home.

A small shopping area but packed with lots of reasonable pricing stalls. They even have 2 local coffee stalls - Toast Box and Ya Kun. The 2 storeys of shops have many eateries outlets and also clothes outlets too.
